<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,853,1130]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,853,878]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="De Deckker, 1981" authorityName="De Deckker" authorityYear="1981" box="[276,749,853,878]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Ilyodromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amplicolis">
<emphasis box="[276,530,853,877]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Ilyodromus amplicolis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="De" box="[540,749,853,878]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="De Deckker, P. (1981) Ostracoda from Australian inland waters - notes on taxonomy and ecology. Proceedings of the Royal Society of Victoria, 93, 43 - 85." type="journal article" year="1981">De Deckker, 1981</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was described from a granite rock pool on top of Boyagin Rock, between Brookton and Pingelly, 
<collectingRegion box="[609,816,889,914]" country="Australia" name="Western Australia" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<collectingRegion box="[609,700,890,913]" country="American Samoa" name="Western" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Western</collectingRegion>
<collectingCountry box="[711,816,889,914]" name="Australia" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Australia</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[832,935,889,914]" name="Australia" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Australia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="De" box="[953,1164,889,914]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="De Deckker, P. (1981) Ostracoda from Australian inland waters - notes on taxonomy and ecology. Proceedings of the Royal Society of Victoria, 93, 43 - 85." type="journal article" year="1981">De Deckker 1981</bibRefCitation>
). The species was then redescribed in Shearn 
<emphasis box="[412,472,925,949]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[492,582,926,949]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">in press</emphasis>
) to enable more detailed comparisons with other species that were more recently described using a larger set of characters (
<bibRefCitation author="Shearn" box="[773,1003,961,986]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Shearn, R., Halse, S. A., Koenders, A., Schon, I. &amp; Martens, K. (2014) Redescriptions of six species of Ilyodromus Sars, 1894 (Crustacea, Ostracoda, Cyprididae) from Eastern Australia and New Zealand. Zootaxa, 3878 (2), 101 - 145. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3878.2.1" type="journal article" year="2014">
Shearn 
<emphasis box="[867,930,961,985]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith" box="[1022,1240,961,986]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Smith, R. J., Janz, H. &amp; Okubo, I. (2011) Recent Cyprididae and Ilyocyprididae (Crustacea: Ostracoda) from Lake Biwa, Japan, including a summary of the lake's ostracod fauna. Zootaxa, 2874, 1 - 37." type="journal article" year="2011">
Smith 
<emphasis box="[1102,1165,961,985]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
). The species is characterised as being large (around 2000 Âµm in length), with a broad calcified inner lamella posteriorly and anteriorly in both valves, without lists or a selvage, very reduced natatory setae on the A2, and the CR with Sp claw-like but with serration on all sides, and bent at 2/3 from the base (
<bibRefCitation author="De" box="[979,1187,1069,1094]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="De Deckker, P. (1981) Ostracoda from Australian inland waters - notes on taxonomy and ecology. Proceedings of the Royal Society of Victoria, 93, 43 - 85." type="journal article" year="1981">De Deckker 1981</bibRefCitation>
). The following three species are allocated to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Deckker" authorityYear="1981" box="[454,703,1105,1129]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Ilyodromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amplicolis">
<emphasis box="[454,703,1105,1129]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Ilyodromus amplicolis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group based on these shared features, and their genetic similarity.
</paragraph>
